    &lt;CommentText&gt;This is more related to clinical assessment unit at chelsea.  
I think rmh is a wonderful hospital and is amazng. That was until my procedure was cancelled and  there was a no beds to stay overnight to have procedure  first thing the following morning.  I was  most distraught. It must be remembered curtains don't retain sound. When in such a dreadful situation you don't want to hear your such light hearted banter. Eventually my concerns was acknowledged and sorted, but I was so upset.
The problem seems to be a lack of beds available in such a case. The private practice from abroad seems to have more and more facilities when really a NHS based hospital.
I would like to thank all staff inc the imaging department which hardly get s recognised as hidden away on their floor.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
